  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing the 6-Month NHI Wait</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You must have 6 months of consecutive residence before enrolling in NHI. Time outside Taiwan resets the clock. Plan accordingly with private insurance.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Misunderstanding Income Requirements</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">It's NT$160,000/month (~$5,000) in your most recent taxable year, not current income. You need documentation proving past income, not just current contracts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Choosing Wrong Duration</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">3-year card costs only slightly more than 1-year but saves reapplication hassle. If you're uncertain, the 2-year card offers good balance.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Collecting Card Promptly</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You have 30 days after approval to pick up your card. Missing this deadline can void your approval. Plan your arrival accordingly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Summer Humidity</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Taiwan summers (June-September) are hot and humid. Typhoons are common. If you're sensitive to heat, consider timing or choose an apartment with good AC.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

