  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What if I don't earn $5,000/month?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          You may qualify via the expertise path if you have professional achievements: publications, patents, awards, significant portfolio work, or conference presentations in your field. The "Digital Economy" category is particularly flexible for tech workers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does the 6-month NHI wait work?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          You must reside consecutively in Taiwan for 6 months. Trips outside Taiwan pause the countdown. After 6 months, you're required to enroll in NHI—it's not optional. Until then, use private international insurance.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I work for Taiwanese companies with the Gold Card?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes! The Gold Card includes an open work permit—you can work for any employer without restrictions, including Taiwanese companies. You can also freelance, consult, or run your own business.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Taiwan's NHI really that good?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Taiwan's NHI is consistently ranked top 3 globally for efficiency and coverage. At $25-50/month, you get comprehensive coverage including dental and traditional Chinese medicine. Wait times are minimal—you can often see a specialist same-day.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need to speak Mandarin?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Not required but helpful. English proficiency is growing, especially among younger Taiwanese and in tech. Major hospitals have English services. Daily life is manageable with translation apps, but basic Mandarin greatly enhances your experience.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can the Gold Card lead to permanent residency?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. After 5 years of consecutive residence (183+ days/year), you can apply for permanent residency. The Gold Card is a clear pathway to long-term status in Taiwan.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

